# Supabase Rules for AI

## Setup
- Supabase JS SDK for client-side queries
- Client config in `src/lib/supabase/client.js`
- Database migrations in `supabase/migrations/`
- Edge functions in `supabase/functions/`

## Patterns
- Use the Supabase JS client for all DB operations
- Use realtime subscriptions for live events
- Use Row Level Security (RLS) on all tables
- Edge functions for server-side logic (anti-cheat, event scheduling)

## Auth
- Support Steam, Google, Apple login (configured in Supabase dashboard)
- Store auth state client-side
- Use RLS policies that check auth.uid()

## Database
- PostgreSQL with relational schema
- Use migrations for schema changes (never modify directly)
- JSON columns for flexible game data (event configs, shape buffs)
- Timestamps on all tables (created_at, updated_at)

## Not Yet Set Up
- Supabase is planned but not connected yet
- For now, game saves to localStorage only
- When ready: `npm install @supabase/supabase-js`
